1 A BILL for an Act to create and enact a new section to chapter 39-05 of the North Dakota
2 Century Code, relating to a request for a certificate of title for a motor vehicle.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. A new section to chapter 39-05 of the North Dakota Century Code is created
5 and enacted as follows:
6 Request for certificate of title - Nonlegal owner.
7 1. If a motor vehicle, which has been issued a certificate of title, has not been registered
8 under chapter 39 - 04 for more than ten years, and an individual, who is not the lega l
9 owner, requests a certificate of title, the individual requesting the certificate of title
10 shall:
11 a. Send a certified letter to the last-known address at which the motor vehicle was
12 registered.
13 b. Advertise for fourteen days a notice of the vehicle title request in a newspaper of
14 general circulation in the county in which the vehicle was last registered.
15 2. If the individual requesting the certificate of title does not receive a response within
16 fourteen days and provides the department with satisfactory proof of compliance with
17 this section, the department shall issue a certificate of title to the individual under
18 section 39 - 05 - 09 .
